NUS Esports @ NUS E-Gaming_200717.info:
It&rsquo;s the Summer Holidays and you&rsquo;re lowkey bored at home. Phase 2 only allows you to visit 4 other friends, and that sucks cos you really want to hang out with loads of people, especially people who have similar interests. Wellllll&hellip; LOOK NO FURTHER!&nbsp;
NUSEG is proud to present Summer Jam 2020 this Summer break :D Take part in our upcoming online community event, Summer Jam from July 17 to July 19! We will be featuring your favourite games (League of Legends, Dota 2, Super Smash Bros, and Mobile Legends) as well as Riot Games&rsquo; new tactical shooter, Valorant for the first time!
SIGN UP NOW: bit.ly/nusegsummerjam&nbsp;
First 10 signups will be eligible to receive $10 vouchers from Legendary HK Restaurant!&nbsp;
Note this event is only open to NUSEG members, please ensure you are a registered member on nusync (bit.ly/nusegaming) before signing up for the event üòä
The theme for this event will be custom gamemodes. Players of all skill levels are encouraged to join as there will be much fun times to be had in our custom games.
All participants also stand a chance to win prizes worth up to $400 in our daily events and raffle! If recording your exciting gameplay or hilarious bloopers is your thing, we will also be accepting submissions and rewarding the top 5 clips from Summer Jam with Creative Stage Air Bluetooth speakers worth $60.
Follow our social media pages for more information
https://www.facebook.com/NUSEGaming&nbsp;
https://www.instagram.com/nusegaming/&nbsp;

