NUS Literary Society_200701.info:
Pix(ell)ated 2020 is NUS&rsquo; English Language and Literature Camp, hosted by the NUS Literary Society and NUS Linguistics Interest Group.&nbsp;The camp is open to freshmen across ALL majors, including (but not limited to) English Language, English Literature and Theatre Studies.&nbsp;
Learn about what life as a freshman in NUS is like through informative module talks, online tool orientations and Q&amp;A segments with seniors! Additionally, you&rsquo;ll get to make friends with fellow freshmen and bond through fun programmes and games! Sign ups close 28 June, Sunday.
&nbsp;
For updates on the camp, follow @NUSLiterarySociety and @NUSLinguistics on Instagram!
Date: 1-3 July, 10am-4pm&nbsp;
Venue: Online
Cost: FREE!&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Please feel free to contact any of the following people for more information or if you have any questions!
Project Director: Wee Shyan (92395883)
Vice Project Director/Chief Safety Officer: Lydia (91807945)
Programmes Heads: Dena (83996925) and Desmond (8468 9958)

