NUS Students' Community Service Club_200.info:
About Project C.A.N.
Project C.A.N. stands for Collection in Aid of the Needy, though this year, the definition of our project title will further extend to include Care Packs in Appreciation of our Nurses amidst the COVID-19 pandemic.
&nbsp;
This year, Project C.A.N. XVII aims to target both the financially underprivileged and our healthcare workers. The financially underprivileged have been greatly affected during the COVID-19 pandemic, with many facing additional financial burden, arising from the loss of livelihoods. Our healthcare workers have worked tirelessly without complaining, fighting to give their all, while working with a high risk of contracting COVID-19.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Through establishing an online fundraising platform, our project aims to gather collective community efforts to provide support for the financially underprivileged and show appreciation and encouragement for our healthcare heroes amidst tough times.
&nbsp;
Our Fundraising Efforts
Financially Underprivileged Families [Target Amount: $22,000]

Provide $40 worth of supermarket vouchers for each of the 550 households under ComCare Assistance residing in Nee Soon East, in collaboration with Nee Soon East Youth Network
On top of these supermarket vouchers, an assistance booklet with relevant information and helplines will be provided for them to seek further assistance if required

&nbsp;
*oscar@sg fund will match funds collected for underprivileged families, dollar for dollar, for the first $10,000 collected
*Any additional funds raised would allow us to reach out to more underprivileged families
&nbsp;
Healthcare Heroes [Target Amount: $5,000]

With a $2 for 1 Healthcare Hero concept, funds collected will be used to prepare a small care pack for our healthcare heroes to show gratitude for their sacrifices
Personalised appreciation notes will be given to each healthcare hero&nbsp;
Items within the care pack will be purchased from our local small businesses, who might be struggling during this period&nbsp;
Targeted to distribute care packs to 2,500 healthcare heroes across various nursing homes

&nbsp;
*oscar@sg fund will match funds collected for our healthcare heroes, dollar for dollar, for the first $2,000 collected
*Any additional funds raised would allow us to reach out to more healthcare heroes
&nbsp;
How Can You Help?&nbsp;
Donate today:&nbsp;bit.ly/canfundraise
Write your appreciation notes here:&nbsp;bit.ly/canhealthcareheroes
&nbsp;
For More Information:
Refer to our fundraising FAQs:&nbsp;bit.ly/canfaqs
Join our telegram channel for updates:&nbsp;bit.ly/cantele
&nbsp;
*Please take note that Tax Deductible Receipts (TDR) are not issued. If you require a TDR, please kindly email nuscsc.projectcan@gmail.com and we will get back to you within 1-3 working days on an alternative donation process.
*If you have any other questions, please feel free to drop us an email at nuscsc.projectcan@gmail.com or drop us a Whatsapp message at 8759 7971.

